&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paediatric Clinical Psychology - Psychological Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Consultant Clinical Psychologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;0.6 WTE Band 8D Clinical Psychologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;12 months secondment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced consultant-level clinical psychologist for a 12-month secondment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The paediatric clinical psychology service provides a specialist psychological service to a range of medical teams within Addenbrookes’ Hospital. This is a large team comprised of clinical psychologists, counsellor practitioners a Child &amp; Adolescent Psychiatrist and an Art Therapist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will provide clinical and operational leadership to the team, including the Cambridge Centre for Paediatric Neuro-Rehabilitation Services (CCPNR) and work closely with the service manager to ensure the smooth operational running of the service and that service contractual obligations are met. The ideal candidate will have a strong team work ethic and an ability to work under pressure. They will be accountable for the professional and clinical leadership of the service and must be able to prioritise their workload and show a high degree of adaptability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is expected to start in early 2021 to cover a planned employment break and this is a 0.6 WTE, 12 month seconded post. This is an excellent career development opportunity, and the successful candidate will be supported by senior colleagues. The post holder will have excellent organisational and inter-personal skills and support the development of effective working relationships and systems across the wide range of services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gwen Hughes service Manager, Liaison psychiatry&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gwen.Hughes@cpft.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
